  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Hazard forecasts to a large extent rely on numerical weather prediction (NWP), which have improved tremendously over the past decades 17.",
    "However, challenges remain: For example, with fast-onset disasters such as storms and floods, accurate forecasting of precipitation is necessary, a fact that involves resolving convection, which is computationally slow in NWP models.",
    "Hence, for such disasters, lead times can be fairly short, sometimes too short for effective action 18.",
    "For instance, in late 2021 the tropical cyclone Rai struck the Philippines.",
    "It had undergone an unforeseen very rapid intensification in the hours before landfall, and hence early action mechanisms had not been triggered 19."
  ],
